The paper deals with the problem of feature selection, which is a common task in machine learning and data analysis. The proposed method involves a unified learning framework that performs structure learning and feature selection simultaneously. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories in computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and data mining (cs.DM). Among these, cs.LG is the most likely category as it deals with the general problem of learning from data, which includes feature selection. The other categories are also relevant as they involve tasks that often require feature selection, such as image and text analysis.
